text: Kirovsky () is a rural locality (a village) in Ulu-Telyaksky Selsoviet, Iglinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 72 as of 2010. There are 5 streets. == Geography == It is located 72 km from Iglino, 2 km from Ulu-Telyak. == References == Category:Rural localities in Iglinsky District
title: Kirovsky, Republic of Bashkortostan
